  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "AI System Prompt Management — Admin Settings Page\n\nBuild an admin settings page that gives users full visibility and control over the AI system prompts powering their Krisp experience, enabling them to fine-tune how their Open Brain and AI features interpret, classify, and respond to their personal context.\n\nRequirements:\n\n**Settings Page Structure**\n- Add a new \"AI & Prompts\" section within the existing settings or admin area\n- Display a list of all system prompts in use across the application, grouped by feature (e.g., Open Brain / MCP Retrieval, Meeting Intelligence Search, Daily Briefing, Decision Register, Email Extraction, Card Priority Suggestions, etc.)\n- Each prompt entry shows: feature name, a short description of what the prompt controls, the current active prompt text, and last-modified timestamp\n\n**Prompt Viewing**\n- Render each system prompt in a readable, syntax-highlighted or monospace code block\n- Allow the user to expand/collapse individual prompts to avoid visual clutter\n- Show a \"default\" badge when the prompt matches the original factory default\n\n**Prompt Editing**\n- Provide an inline editor (leveraging the existing @uiw/react-md-editor or a plain monospace textarea) for each prompt\n- Include a character/token count indicator to help users stay within model context limits\n- Validate that the prompt is non-empty before saving\n- Require an explicit \"Save Changes\" confirmation action per prompt — no auto-save\n- On save, persist the custom prompt to the Neon PostgreSQL database tied to the authenticated user, so it survives sessions and deployments\n\n**Reset & Safety**\n- Offer a \"Reset to Default\" button per prompt that restores the original factory value after a confirmation dialog\n- Maintain the factory defaults as constants in the codebase (not database-dependent) so resets are always possible\n- Display a warning banner if a saved prompt deviates significantly in length or structure from the default, as a guardrail against accidental breakage\n\n**Runtime Integration**\n- All existing AI-powered features that currently use hardcoded system prompts must read from the database at request time, falling back to the hardcoded default if no user customization exists\n- Ensure prompt resolution is consistent across server actions, API routes, and MCP tool handlers\n\n**Audit & History**\n- Store a lightweight version history (last 5 versions) per prompt so users can view previous values and revert to any prior version without needing to retype\n- Log each prompt change to the existing immutable audit trail\n\n**Edge Cases**\n- If a user's custom prompt causes an AI call to fail (e.g., model refusal, malformed output), surface a clear error in the relevant feature UI and include a link back to the prompt settings page\n- Ensure prompt editing is accessible only to the authenticated account owner — no prompt data is exposed to unauthenticated requests\n- Handle concurrent edits gracefully (last-write-wins with timestamp, or optimistic lock conflict message)",
  "title": "Add AI system prompt management to admin settings",
