  "summary": "## Summary: AI System Prompt Management — Admin Settings Page\n\n### Changes Implemented\n\n**Database Layer**\n- Added `custom_prompts` table with user_id, prompt_key, prompt_text, version, timestamps, and unique constraint on (user_id, prompt_key)\n- Added `custom_prompt_history` table for version history (last 5 versions) per prompt\n- Created SQL migration `0024_add-custom-prompts.sql`\n\n**Prompt Registry & Resolution**\n- Created `lib/ai/prompts.ts` — central registry of all 15 system prompts organized by feature category, each with a unique key, name, description, category, and factory default text\n- Created `lib/ai/resolvePrompt.ts` — resolution layer that reads user's custom prompt from DB, falling back to factory default if none exists or on DB error\n\n**API Routes**\n- `GET /api/settings/prompts` — returns all prompt definitions merged with user customizations\n- `PUT /api/settings/prompts` — saves a custom prompt with version tracking, history logging, and history pruning (keeps last 5)\n- `DELETE /api/settings/prompts` — resets a prompt to factory default by removing the custom record and history\n- `GET /api/settings/prompts/history?key=` — returns version history for a specific prompt\n\n**Admin UI Page**\n- New page at `/admin/prompts` with server-side auth via `getRequiredUser()`\n- `PromptsClient.tsx` — full-featured client component with:\n  - Category filter tabs (All, Brain & Knowledge, Meeting Intelligence, Email Processing, etc.)\n  - Expandable/collapsible prompt cards showing name, description, custom/default badge, version, and last-modified date\n  - Inline monospace editor with character and approximate token count\n  - Explicit \"Save Changes\" button (no auto-save), with validation for non-empty text\n  - \"Reset to Default\" with confirmation dialog\n  - Warning banner when custom prompt deviates significantly (>50%) in length from default\n  - Version history panel with restore capability (last 5 versions)\n  - Toast notifications for save/reset/error feedback\n\n**Runtime Integration — All 15 prompts now use `resolvePrompt()`:**\n- `lib/brain/chat.ts` — Brain chat assistant (PROMPT_BRAIN_CHAT)\n- `app/api/brain/chat/route.ts` — Brain chat API (PROMPT_BRAIN_CHAT_API)\n- `lib/brain/intentParser.ts` — Intent classifier (PROMPT_INTENT_CLASSIFIER), added optional userId param\n- `lib/actions/extractActionItems.ts` — Meeting action items (PROMPT_ACTION_ITEMS_MEETING)\n- `lib/actions/extractDecisions.ts` — Meeting & email decisions (PROMPT_DECISIONS_MEETING, PROMPT_DECISIONS_EMAIL)\n- `lib/actions/extractEmailActions.ts` — Email action items (PROMPT_EMAIL_ACTIONS), added optional userId param\n- `lib/email/classifyEmail.ts` — Email classification (PROMPT_EMAIL_CLASSIFY)\n- `lib/weekly-review/generate.ts` — Weekly review analyst (PROMPT_WEEKLY_REVIEW), added userId passthrough\n- `app/api/brain/clips/route.ts` — Web clip metadata (PROMPT_WEB_CLIP_META)\n- `app/api/integrations/zapier/ingest/route.ts` — Zapier ingest metadata (PROMPT_ZAPIER_INGEST_META)\n- `app/api/search/route.ts` — Search optimizer & answer (PROMPT_SEARCH_OPTIMIZER, PROMPT_SEARCH_ANSWER)\n- `app/api/action-items/generate-cards/route.ts` — Card generation (PROMPT_GENERATE_CARDS)\n- `app/api/v1/boards/[boardId]/priority-review/route.ts` — Priority review (PROMPT_PRIORITY_REVIEW)\n\n**Navigation**\n- Added \"AI Prompts\" nav item with icon in SideNav, between Integrations and Trash\n\n### Files Modified\n- `lib/db/schema.ts` — added custom_prompts and custom_prompt_history tables\n- `lib/brain/chat.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for brain chat\n- `lib/brain/intentParser.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for intent classification, added userId param\n- `lib/actions/extractActionItems.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for meeting action extraction\n- `lib/actions/extractDecisions.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for meeting/email decision extraction\n- `lib/actions/extractEmailActions.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for email action extraction, added userId param\n- `lib/email/classifyEmail.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for email classification\n- `lib/weekly-review/generate.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for weekly review, added userId passthrough\n- `app/api/brain/chat/route.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for brain chat API, passes userId to classifyIntent\n- `app/api/brain/clips/route.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for web clip metadata\n- `app/api/integrations/zapier/ingest/route.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for zapier metadata\n- `app/api/search/route.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for search optimizer and answer\n- `app/api/action-items/generate-cards/route.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for card generation\n- `app/api/v1/boards/[boardId]/priority-review/route.ts` — uses resolvePrompt for priority review\n- `components/ui/SideNav.tsx` — added AI Prompts nav item with icon and route matching\n\n### Files Created\n- `lib/ai/prompts.ts` — prompt registry with 15 factory defaults\n- `lib/ai/resolvePrompt.ts` — DB-backed prompt resolution with fallback\n- `app/api/settings/prompts/route.ts` — CRUD API for custom prompts\n- `app/api/settings/prompts/history/route.ts` — version history API\n- `app/(app)/admin/prompts/page.tsx` — server component page\n- `app/(app)/admin/prompts/PromptsClient.tsx` — client component with full UI\n- `drizzle/migrations/0024_add-custom-prompts.sql` — database migration\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- Run the migration `0024_add-custom-prompts.sql` against the database before deploying\n- The TypeScript check passes with no new errors (only pre-existing `.next` cache issue)\n- All existing AI features fall back to factory defaults if no custom prompt exists, ensuring zero-downtime deployment\n- The `resolvePrompt()` function includes a try/catch that returns the default if the DB query fails, providing graceful degradation\n- Optional userId parameters were used for backward compatibility on functions called from contexts without userId (e.g., extractEmailActions)"
}